{"cursor":"4808","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox MLB player |name=Horace Clarke |image= |position=Second baseman\n|bats=Switch |throws=Right |birth_date= |birth_place=Frederiksted, St. Croix,\nUnited States Virgin Islands |debutdate=May 13 |debutyear=1965 |debutteam=New\nYork Yankees |finaldate=September 15 |finalyear=1974 |finalteam=San Diego\nPadres |stat1label=Batting average |stat1value=.256 |stat2label=Hits\n|stat2value=1,230 |stat3label=Runs batted in |stat3value=304\n|teams= *New York Yankees (â) *San Diego Padres () }} 'Horace\nMeredith Clarke' (born June 2, 1940, in Frederiksted, St. Croix, United States\nVirgin Islands) was a Major League Baseball player for the New York Yankees and\nthe San Diego Padres from 1965 to 1974.\n\nHe was signed by the Yankees as an amateur free agent in 1958. He made his Major\nLeague Baseball debut on May 13, 1965. In 1967, he became the Yankees' regular\nsecond baseman upon the retirement of longtime veteran Bobby Richardson. In 10\nseasons, he hit .256, with 27 home runs and 304 RBI. In the space of one month\nin 1970, he broke up three possible no-hitters in the ninth inning (Jim Rooker [http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=Yv1XAAAAIBAJ&sjid=C_cDAAAAIBAJ&pg=177-\n1,435887&dq=jim+rooker+horace+clarke&hl=en Royals lose in 12 innings; Rooker\nblows no-hit game] on June 4, Sonny Siebert [http://news.google.com/n-\newspapers?id=PHUfAAAAIBAJ&sjid=YigEAAAAIBAJ&pg=1420,5119500&dq=sonny+siebert+ho-\nrace+clarke&hl=en Clarke spoils 2nd no-hitter] on June 19 and, Joe Niekro-\n[http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=hwMqAAAAIBAJ&sjid=QigEAAAAIBAJ&pg=71-\n05,895757&dq=jim+rooker+horace+clarke&hl=en Clarke the spoiler ruins 3rd no-\nhitter] on July 2). That season, Clarke made 732 plate appearances\n(batting 686 times officially). As a fielder, though, the knock on Clarke was\nthat he would not turn the double play with runners barreling in. Few ever took\nhim out with a slide, but Clarke would hold the ball after leaping.\n\nClarke was sold to the San Diego Padres on May 31, 1974, for $25,000. He retired\nat the end of the 1974 season. After his retirement, he worked as a baseball\ninstructor for the Virgin Islands Department of Recreation and as an assistant\nscout for the Kansas City Royals.\n\nClarke and Joe Mauer are the only hitters ever to break up three no-hitter bids\nin the ninth inning.[http://milkeespress.com/lostninth.html]\n","linknr":144,"url":"Horace_Clarke","recorded":1375076666,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Horace_Clarke&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Horace_Clarke&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Second_baseman","/wiki/Frederiksted","/wiki/St._Croix","/wiki/United_States_Virgin_Islands","/wiki/Batting_average","/wiki/Hit_(baseball)","/wiki/Run_batted_in","/wiki/New_York_Yankees","/wiki/1965_in_baseball","/wiki/1974_in_baseball","/wiki/San_Diego_Padres","/wiki/1974_in_baseball","/wiki/Frederiksted","/wiki/St._Croix","/wiki/United_States_Virgin_Islands","/wiki/Major_League_Baseball","/wiki/New_York_Yankees","/wiki/San_Diego_Padres","/wiki/Yankees","/wiki/Major_League_Baseball","/wiki/Yankees","/wiki/Second_baseman","/wiki/Bobby_Richardson","/wiki/Home_run","/wiki/RBI","/wiki